📦 FOLDER STRUCTURE

e-commerce-website-with-admin-panel/
├── e-commerce/ # Project settings
├── shop/ # Main app with models, views, templates
├── static/ # Static files (CSS, JS, images)
├── templates/ # HTML templates
├── media/ # Uploaded product images
├── db.sqlite3 # Database
├── Pipfile # Dependencies
└── manage.py # Django management script

---

🚀 GETTING STARTED

Follow these steps to run this project locally.

---

1️⃣ Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/harishankar/e-commerce-website-with-admin-panel.git
cd e-commerce-website-with-admin-panel

---

2️⃣ Create and Activate a Virtual Environment

python -m venv venv

For Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate

For macOS/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate

---

3️⃣ Install Required Packages

pip install -r requirements.txt

---

4️⃣ Run Migrations

python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate

---

5️⃣ Create a Superuser for Admin Access

python manage.py createsuperuser

---

6️⃣ Run the Server

python manage.py runserver
Now open your browser and go to http://127.0.0.1:8000/

---

🔐 ADMIN ACCESS

Visit: http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin

Log in using the superuser credentials you created above

From here, you can manage products, categories, users, and orders

